California Department of Social Services (CDSS) – Large Language Model (LLM) Research
As part of Harris Policy Labs Project

As part of a research initiative with the California Department of Social Services, I contributed to the 
development and evaluation of a Large Language Model (LLM)-based solution designed to support policy and 
program analysis. My work involved researching generative AI applications in the public sector, evaluating 
model performance, designing prompts and testing workflows, and identifying opportunities to improve the 
accessibility and efficiency of policy-related information.

We were tasked with devising an efficient way to analyse the county self-assessment reports which are produced every year.
Through this project, I gained hands-on experience applying emerging AI technologies to real-world government 
challenges while considering the importance of accuracy, transparency, and responsible AI in public service.


